news.title: UK: Persimmon's pretax profit dips 52% to $450.5 million in 2023
news.para: Shares in the FTSE 100 firm slipped more than 3% to 1,328 pence in early trading, the biggest decliner on the blue-chip index in percentage terms.

news.title: Germany's TAG Immobilien posts net loss of 410.9 million euros in 2023
news.para: The loss followed further writedowns in the value of its property holdings, and the company said it would suspend dividend payments for the second consecutive year to strengthen its capital position.

news.title: South Korea's land minister bearish on property as population ages
news.para: South Korea's land minister says the country won't see a repeat of the sharp home price gains as its population rapidly ages and economy slows. The minister vows to promote public rental accommodation to improve access to housing. .

news.title: China's first two consumption-related REITs close roughly flat on debut
news.para: The two real estate investment trusts listed in Shanghai are backed by shopping centres owned by developer China Jinmao and supermarkets owned by retailer Wumart.

news.title: China Vanke's bonds eased after Moody's starts ratings review
news.para: Vanke's Hong Kong-listed shares opened down 1%, though they strengthened to climbed 1.4% as of 0229 GMT, while its Shenzhen-listed shares dropped 0.4%.

news.title: Madhya Pradesh HC quashes order for land acquisition of 35 people in scheme 114
news.para: The appeals deserve to be and are accordingly allowed. The notification under Section 4(1) & 6(1) of the Act, 1894 and the consequent award dated 27.11.1992 only in so far as the same relates to the present appellants are hereby quashed,” the court held.

news.title: Tamil Nadu: TNHUDB increases building height
news.para: The amendment also exempts buildings with eight dwelling units from requiring completion certificates, making it easier to obtain water supply and electricity connections. Builders are skeptical about implementation.

news.title: Pune civic body starts special call centre to recover property tax
news.para: The civic body has set a target of making 50,000 calls a month. It is the first such attempt by the Pune Municipal Corporation (PMC) to directly interact with small tax defaulters through a dedicated call centre.

news.title: Indore civic body razes six illegal houses in ward 17
news.para: Acting on instructions of IMC commissioner Harshika Singh, the civic body’s removal team on Monday reached Anjani Nagar that was illegally being developed in ward 17 under Zone 4.

news.title: Citizens oppose C&D waste dumping near lake
news.para: According to Poongothai Paramasivam, a resident and member of the Bengaluru Navanirman Party, there is a lack of clarity on the current lake boundary. While the waterbody has been fenced by the BBMP, it extends beyond the fence, leading to confusion.

news.title: Maharashtra government approves metro extension on Wagholi & Chandni Chowk sections
news.para: Maha Metro officials said the Ramwadi-Wagholi extension would cover a distance of 11.63km and have 12 stations, while the Vanaz-Chandni Chowk stretch will cover 1.12km with two stations.

news.title: Collector's guidelines to increase in 50% areas of Indore from April 1
news.para: The new rates will be implemented from April 1, 2024, and have seen an increase ranging from 20% to 100% in approximately 2,450 areas out of a total of around 5,000 in the state's commercial capital.

news.title: Maharashtra govt to provide Rs 3,000 crore, BMC to give Rs 1,500 crore for mill workers' homes
news.para: The decision comes on the eve of the Lok Sabha elections. For the last eight months, the government has sought applications from mill workers and their heirs for free housing.

news.title: Will study Gujarat model to ensure timely recovery of dues: Maharashtra housing minister
news.para: The Union ministry of housing and urban affairs had earlier directed states to follow the ‘Gujarat model’ amid poor recovery order execution, My department will study the Gujarat model as suggested by the Centre.

news.title: Gujarat RERA forms mediation panel
news.para: The authority stated in a letter, “More than 500 complaints are being received by this authority from allottees under Section 31 of the Act for issues such as refund, interest, sale deed, possession, common amenities, repairs and compensation.

news.title: Byju’s to vacate several offices in cost-cutting drive, may give up HQ partially
news.para: Byju's is undergoing a cost-cutting initiative and restructuring drive, downsizing assets and tuition centers. The edtech firm has identified assets that overlap with its Aakash centres.

news.title: Government asks large banks to support China Vanke in rare intervention: Sources
news.para: The State Council - China's cabinet - is coordinating support effort for China Vanke , said the sources with direct knowledge of the matter, adding financial institutions have been requested to make swift progress.

news.title: British Land names William Rucker as chair-designate
news.para: Rucker, 60, the current chairman of asset manager Intermediate Capital Group, had held the role at housebuilder Crest Nicholson as well for more than seven years till 2018.
